cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the calibration of multiple LiDARs on a mobile platform for localization and perception systems, which are common topics in robotics research.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper proposes an appearance-based method for refining the calibration parameters using point-plane correspondences, which is a common technique in computer vision.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper may use machine learning techniques for the hand-eye calibration and/or the appearance-based refinement.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper may use AI techniques for the hand-eye calibration and/or the appearance-based refinement.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the calibration of a multi-LiDAR system on a mobile platform, which involves control and system integration aspects.
